  <span id="freeText706333835582296644" style="display:none">Difficult to "enter" in this novel without some precision especially on the work of Pessoa to whom Saramago leaves here a beautiful tribute: Pessoa had the particularity of creating not only characters from the novel but also authors of heteronyms with whom he exchanges, with whom he argues that he protects and who are entirely part of his work. In fact, the writer has since his first texts shown an appetite for madness, schizophrenia and double personalities, from this meeting imagined by Saramago between Pessoa and his "other".</span>
